result.execSummary:
The defendant Jennifer M Palfrey was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Burglary-Building or Dwelling [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.10(1m)(a).
  • Attempt Burglary-Dwelling/Boat w/ Person Present [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class E felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.10(2)(e).

10:12 AM Defendant Jennifer M Palfrey in court with attorney David J Susens.  Rick C Spoentgen appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court states case and parties state appearances.  Atty Susens states agreement.  Parties discuss error on information.  Court goes off the record so parties can clarify the correct charges.  Back on the record the State has now provided an amended information and parties have reviewed VIS.  Parties agree.  Court questions DE on agreement.  DE agrees and pleads NC to both counts.  Court questions DE on pleas.  DE advised of voting rights and felony firearms and body armor warnings.  State makes statement re: restitution being paid in full by co-DE prior to today and notes serious felony warnings might be given also as Count 2 is considered a serious felony.  Recess for Atty Susens to talk to his client outside the presence of the courtroom.  Back on the record at 11:16 a.m. Atty Susens makes record re: his discussion w/DE re: three strikes implications as to serious felonies.  DE states she understands and the Court continues questioning her re: potential penalties on the serious felony issue.  Parties are in agreement that there are no prior serious felonies on her record.  Court accepts pleas and finds DE guilty.  State makes statement re: recommendations.  Atty Susens makes statement re: recommendations.  Court admonishes DE and sentences.
